On the likelihood approxiamtion and the join distribution

Another way to write down the join likelihood function is

\[\begin{equation} \label{lik2} f_X(x,y;\phi) = \underbrace{\left(\prod_{i=1}^{d} e^{-s_i\left[\Delta t_i-\frac{e^{-T\mu_0}}{\mu_0} (e^{\Delta t_i \mu_0}-1)\right]}\right)}_\text{missing speciations}\underbrace{\left(\prod_{i=1}^{d} e^{-s_i\frac{e^{-T \mu_0}}{\mu_0}(e^{\Delta t_i \mu_0}-1)} \right)}_\text{extant speciations}\underbrace{\left(\prod_{i=1}^{d} e^{-\mu_0n_i \Delta t_{i}}\right)}_\text{extinctions}\underbrace{\left( \prod_{i=1}^{d-1} \rho_i \right)}_\text{topology} \end{equation}\]

where

\[\rho_i= \begin{cases} \lambda_{j} & \text{if speciation of species j takes place at time } t_i \\ \mu_{0} & \text{if extinction of species j takes place at time } t_i \end{cases} \]

the probability density of the missing part of the tree would be then

\[\begin{equation} \label{sak2} g_X(x;\phi) = \underbrace{\left(\prod_{i=1}^{d} e^{-s_i\left[\Delta t_i-\frac{e^{-T\mu_0}}{\mu_0} ( e^{\Delta t_i \mu_0}-1)\right]}\right)}_\text{missing speciations}\underbrace{\left(\prod_{i=1}^{d} e^{-\mu_0 m_i t_{i} }\right)}_\text{extinctions}\underbrace{\left( \prod_{i \in M} \rho_{i} \right)}_\text{missing topology} \end{equation}\]

where \(m_i\) is the number of missing species at time \(t_i\).

We define

\[ w_i = \frac{f_{X,Y}(x,y;\phi)}{g_X(x;\phi)} = \left(\prod_{i=1}^{d} e^{-s_i\frac{e^{-T \mu_0}}{\mu_0}(e^{\Delta t_i \mu_0}-1)} \right)\left(\prod_{i=1}^{d} e^{-o_i \mu_0 \Delta t_{i} }\right)\left( \prod_{i \neq M} \lambda_i \right)\]

where \(M = \{m_1, ... , m_m\}\) and \(o_i\) is the number of observed species at time \(t_i\), so \(n_i = m_i + o_i\)

we_cal <- function(tree){ # weights calculation
  list2env(setNames(tree, c("wt","to","n","s","r","pars","t_ext")), .GlobalEnv)
  mu = pars[2]
  if(mu!=0){
    if(length(t_ext) != length(to)) t_ext = t_ext[-length(t_ext)]#to = c(to,2)
    ev = (to==1 & is.infinite(t_ext))
    nobs = c(2,2+cumsum(ev))
    index = ev
    logg = sum(-s*(exp(-r*mu)/mu)*(exp(wt*mu)-1))+sum(log(s[index]/n[index]))-sum(mu*nobs*wt)
  }else{
    logg = 0
  }
  return(logg)
}

Marginal likelihoods calculation

rm(list = ls())

a1 <- function(vec){
    nvec = vector(mode="numeric",length=2*length(vec))
    ind = seq(from=1,to=2*length(vec),by=2)
    nvec[ind] = vec
    nvec[ind+1] = vec*(-1)
    return(nvec)
}

a2 <- function(vec,k){
  nvec = vector(mode="numeric",length=2*length(vec))
  ind = seq(from=1,to=2*length(vec),by=2)
  nvec[ind] = k+1
  nvec[ind+1] = vec
return(nvec)
}

a3 <- function(vec,v31,k,s){
  nvec = vector(mode="numeric",length=2*length(vec))
  ind = seq(from=1,to=2*length(vec),by=2)
  nvec[ind] = vec*ifelse((s[k+1]-s[k])!=0,(1/(s[k+1]-s[k])),CT)
  nvec[ind+1] = vec*ifelse((s[v31]-s[k])!=0,(1/(s[v31]-s[k])),CT)
  return(nvec)
}

no.na <- function(vector){
  vector[!is.na(vector)]
}

marginalM <- function(M,s,CT,lambda,mu){
  v1 = 1
  v21 = 2*M + 1
  v3 = 1/(s[2*M+1]-s[2*M])
  for (k in (2*M-1):1){
    zeros = which((s[v21]-s[k-1])==0)
    if(length(zeros)>0){
      tempv1 = v1[zeros]
      tempv21 = v21[zeros]
      tempv3 = v3[zeros]
      #tempv3 = ifelse((s[v31]-s[k])!=0,tempv3*(1/(s[v31]-s[k])),CT)
      v1 = v1[-zeros]
      v21 = v21[-zeros]
      v3 = v3[-zeros]
    }
    v1 = a1(v1)
    v3 = a3(v3,v21,k,s)
    v21 = a2(v21,k)
    if(length(zeros)>0){
      v1 = c(v1,tempv1)
      v21 = c(v21,tempv21)
      v3 = c(v3,tempv3,k,s)
    }
  }
  v2 = exp(-CT*s[v21])
  v4 = ifelse((s[v21]-s[1])!=0,exp(CT*(s[v21]-s[1]))-1,1)
  out = sum(v1*v2*v3*v4)*(lambda^M)*(mu^M)
  return(out)
}


get.topologies <- function(M){
  TO = matrix(nrow=2*M,ncol=1)
  TO[1,1] = 1
  for(i in 2:(2*M)){
    comb = ncol(TO)
    for(j in 1:comb){
      ns = sum(no.na(TO[,j]))
      ne = sum(1-no.na(TO[,j]))
      if(ns < M & ns > ne){ #extinction or speciation
        TO[i,j] = 1
        TO = cbind(TO,matrix(TO[,j],ncol=1))
        TO[i,ncol(TO)] = 0
      }
      if(ns == M & ns > ne){ #extinction
        TO[i,j] = 0
      }
      if(ns < M & ns == ne){ #speciation
        TO[i,j] = 1
      }
    }
  }
  return(TO)
}


MargM <- function(M,CT,lambda,mu,trunclast=FALSE){
  NC=NULL
  MA=NULL
  for(m in 1:M){
    tops = get.topologies(m)
    ncomb = NULL
    margs = NULL
    for(j in 1:ncol(tops)){
      to = tops[,j]
      #################
      n = c(2,2+cumsum(to)+cumsum(to-1))
      s = n*ifelse(n!=2,(lambda+mu),lambda)
      if(sum(to)>=M){
        stopspec = min(which(cumsum(to)==M))
        s[(stopspec+1):length(s)] = mu*n[(stopspec+1):length(s)]
      }
      if(m==M & trunclast) s[length(s)] = 0
      n = n[-length(n)]
      n[to==0] = n[to==0]-2
      #################
      ncomb[j] = prod(n)
      margs[j] = marginalM(M = m,s = s,CT = CT,lambda,mu)
    }
    NC = c(NC, ncomb)
    MA = c(MA, margs)
  }
  vals = sum(NC*MA)+exp(-2*lambda*CT)
  return(vals)
}

get.combinations <- function(to){
  n = c(2,2+cumsum(to)+cumsum(to-1))
}

f.marg <- function(tm,lambda,mu){
  ans<-NULL
  if (is.vector(tm)){
    tm<-matrix(tm,nrow=1)
  }
  CT = no.na(tm[1,])[length(no.na(tm[1,]))]
  for (i in 1:nrow(tm)){
    if (tm[i,1] == CT){
      if (3*mu==2*lambda){
        ans[i] = 1 - 2*CT*lambda*exp(-3*mu*CT)
      } else {
        ans[i] = (1 + ((2*lambda*exp(-3*mu*CT))/(3*mu-2*lambda))*(1-exp(CT*(3*mu-2*lambda)))-exp(-2*lambda*CT))/3+exp(-2*lambda*CT)
      }
    } else {
      ans[i] = dexp(tm[i,1],2*lambda)*(1/2)*(exp(-(tm[i,2]-tm[i,1])*3*mu))
    }
  }
  return(ans)
}

h2 <- function(s,CT){
  v1 = c(-1,1,1,-1,1,-1,-1,1)
  v21 = c(s[2],s[3],s[2],s[4],s[2],s[3],s[2],0)
  v2 = exp(-v21*CT)
  v3 = s[4]*c(rep(s[4]-s[3],4),rep(-s[3],4))*c(s[3]-s[2],s[3]-s[2],s[4]-s[2],s[4]-s[2],s[3]-s[2],s[3]-s[2],-s[2],-s[2])
  v4 = ifelse((v21-s[1])!=0, (exp(CT*(v21-s[1]))-1)/(v21-s[1]),CT)
  out = sum((v1*v2*v4)/v3)
  return(out)
}

h1 <- function(s,CT){
  out = (exp(-s[3]*CT)/(s[3]-s[2])) * ( (exp(CT*(s[3]-s[2]))/(s[2]-s[1]))*(exp(CT*(s[2]-s[1]))-1) +
                                          - (1/(s[3]-s[1]))*(exp(CT*(s[3]-s[1]))-1) )
  if(s[1]==s[3]){
    out = (exp(-s[3]*CT)/(s[3]-s[2])) * ( (exp(CT*(s[3]-s[2]))/(s[2]-s[1]))*(exp(CT*(s[2]-s[1]))-1)  - CT )

  }
  return(out)
}

f.marg2S <- function(CT,lambda,mu){
  s1 = c(2,3,4,3)*c(lambda,lambda+mu,mu,mu)
  s2 = c(2,3,2,3)*c(lambda,lambda+mu,lambda,mu)
  s3 = c(2,3,2)*c(lambda,lambda+mu,lambda)
  out = h2(s1,CT)*12*(lambda*mu)^2+h2(s2,CT)*4*(lambda*mu)^2+h1(s3,CT)*2*lambda*mu+exp(-CT*2*lambda)
  return(out)
}

Is the normalized constant influenced by the last bit of the likelihood?

For the likelihood to be normalized we need to calculate the normalization constant

\[ C = \int_{x = \mathcal{X}} f(x|\theta) dx = \int_{x = \mathcal{X}} f(x|\theta) \frac{g(x|\theta)}{g(x|\theta)} = E_{x \sim g} \left[ \frac{f(x|\theta)}{g(x|\theta)} \right] \approx \frac{1}{m} \sum_{i=1}^m \frac{f(x_i|\theta)}{g(x_i|\theta)}\]

norma.const <- function(lambda,mu,CT,n,truncdim = TRUE){
  lg = NULL
  lf = NULL
  for(i in 1:n){
    df = sim.tree.g(lambda,mu,CT) # simulation of tree
    lg[i] = g_samp_missobs(df,c(lambda,mu)) # calculate sampling probability 
    # and calculate joint probability 
    to = df$to[-nrow(df)]
    to[to==2] = 1
    lf[i] = -emphasis:::nllik.tree(pars=c(lambda,mu,Inf),tree=list(wt=diff(c(0,df$bt)),to=to),truncdim = truncdim)
  }
  # finally, get the approximation
  const.approx = sum(exp(lf-lg))/n
  return(const.approx)
}


sim.tree.g <- function(lambda,mu,CT){
  Ne = rpois(1,(lambda+mu)*CT) # number of extinct species
  Np = rpois(1,(lambda-mu)*CT) # number of present species
  brts = runif(Np,min=0,max=CT) # branching times of speciation of present species
  ms = runif(Ne,min=0,max=CT) # branching times of speciation of extinct species
  me = runif(Ne,min=ms,max=CT) # branching times of extinctions
  # return matrix with branching times and topology
  to = c(rep(1,Ne),rep(0,Ne))
  df = data.frame(bt = c(ms,me),to=to)
  df = rbind(df,data.frame(bt=c(brts,CT),to=c(rep(2,length(brts)),2)))
  df = df[order(df$bt),]
  return(df)
}

g_samp_missobs <- function(df,pars){
  # sampling probability 
  last = nrow(df)
  ct = df[last,1]
  Ne = sum(df$to==0)
  Np = sum(df$to==2) - 1
  subdf_e = df[df$to==1,]
  subdf_p = df[df$to==2,]
  Ts = ct-subdf_e$bt
  to = df$to[-last]
  rto = to
  to[to==2] = 1
  n = c(2,2+cumsum(to)+cumsum(to-1))
  nm = n[c(rto,2)==1]
  log_dens_miss = dpois(Ne,lambda =(pars[1]+pars[2])*ct,log=TRUE)-Ne*log(ct)-sum(log(Ts))-sum(log(nm))+lgamma(Ne+1)
  ne = n[c(rto,0)==2]
  log_dens_obs = dpois(Np,lambda = (pars[1]-pars[2])*ct,log=TRUE)-Np*log(ct)-sum(log(ne))+lgamma(Np+1)
  log_dens = log_dens_miss+log_dens_obs
  return(log_dens)
}
